      <title>Recover lost data by simply performing the OST to PST conversion</title>
      <description>&lt;div dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;" trbidi="on"&gt;  &lt;title&gt;&lt;/title&gt;    &lt;style type="text/css"&gt; &lt;!--   @page { margin: 2cm }   P { margin-bottom: 0.21cm }  --&gt;  &lt;/style&gt;   &lt;br /&gt;&lt;div style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"&gt;Presence of corruption in OST file may occur due to various reasons. Whatever may be the reason? Corruption of Outlook OST file is a serious concern which no one can ignore as it can pose major issues later on. The major problem that occurs after corruption of Outlook OST file is inaccessibility of OST data. OST file contains data of objects, such as contacts, e-mail messages, attachments, appointments, tasks, notes, journal, events, etc. Important e-mail operations cannot be carried out at the same time. These all are the difficulties that directly result after OST file corruption. Still, there is no need to be hopeless. Today, several third party tools are available in the market that are enough capable to perform &lt;b&gt;OST to PST&lt;/b&gt; conversion. These tools have been specially designed to perform conversion of OST data into PST.  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"&gt;Below stated are some symptoms that are observed when synchronization of Outlook OST file cannot be carried out easily with Exchange Server:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align="JUSTIFY" style="margin-bottom: 0cm; margin-left: 0.64cm;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;div style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"&gt;Appearance of several error  messages at a time when Outlook OST file in Outlook is synchronized  with your mailbox on a server that is executing MS-Exchange Server.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;div style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"&gt;Absence of some Outlook items,  such as e-mail messages, appointment, contacts, tasks, journal,  events, notes, posted items and documents from Outlook OST file or  from the mailbox once a synchronization of OST file and mailbox is  made.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Cause:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"&gt;Reason behind the occurrence of above mentioned symptoms is a corruption of Outlook OST file. Some other issues related to synchronization of OST file is also the result of OST corruption.  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Solution&lt;/b&gt;:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"&gt;For solving the above stated problematic situation, you have to follow the below stated measures. These measures include:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;div style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"&gt;Use of Scanost.exe tool: Outlook  versions like Outlook 2003 and 2007 make use of an OST Integrity  Check tool to verify the inconsistencies contained in Outlook OST  file. But, Outlook 2010 does not provide any tool to solve errors or  inconsistencies in Outlook OST file as of earlier versions. However,  if there is an issue with a specific folder, then it is suggested to  resync the folder in MS- Outlook 2010. Below stated are the steps:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div style="margin-bottom: 0cm; margin-left: 0.64cm;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;div style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"&gt;Select Properties by doing a   right click on the folder.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;div style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"&gt;Select &lt;b&gt;Clear Offline items&lt;/b&gt;,   and then select &lt;b&gt;OK&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;div style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"&gt;Select the &lt;b&gt;Send/Receive&lt;/b&gt;   tab on the Outlook 2010 ribbon.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;div style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"&gt;Select Update Folder.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"&gt;However, if the problem still remains the same, then it is good to opt for a third party &lt;b&gt;OST PST&lt;/b&gt; converter tool. Yes, number of third party software are easily available online. The best thing is that a facility of a free demo version of the software is available on Internet. You just have to download a demo version of the software. Demo versions help you to evaluate the features of the product easily.  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"&gt;One such tool is &lt;b&gt;Stellar Phoenix Mailbox Exchange Desktop &lt;/b&gt;that is specially designed to &lt;a href="http://osttopstconverter.stellarservertools.com/" target="_blank"&gt;convert OST to PST&lt;/a&gt;. Once OST PST conversion takes place by this tool, data of Outlook OST file can be read into PST format of Microsoft Outlook. Developed with an interactive user interface, the tool is easy to operate. There is no need to have a sound technical knowledge for using this tool.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="blogger-post-footer"&gt;&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/6065906100570324862-490156954671210515?l=ostpstconverter.blogspot.com' alt='' /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/ost-pst-converter/OST_PST_Converter-Recover_lost_data_by_simply_performing_the_OST_to_PST_conversion.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
